# Auto-push for Georgetown Marketplace

After finishing a coherent set of code changes in this project:

1. Stage relevant files (`git add`)
2. Create a concise commit with a HEREDOC message focused on why
3. Push to `origin` (`git push`)

Do this automatically without waiting for the user to ask. Never force-push, never amend unless the user explicitly asks, and never update git config.
